# Sigma API Design Principles Skill

Build intuitive, scalable, and maintainable REST and GraphQL APIs.

## REST Design

### Resource Naming

```
✅ GOOD (Nouns, plural, hierarchical)
GET    /users
GET    /users/{id}
GET    /users/{id}/orders
POST   /organizations/{orgId}/teams/{teamId}/members

❌ BAD (Verbs, actions)
GET    /getUser
POST   /createUser
```

### HTTP Methods

| Method | Purpose | Idempotent |
|--------|---------|------------|
| GET | Retrieve | Yes |
| POST | Create | No |
| PUT | Replace | Yes |
| PATCH | Partial update | No |
| DELETE | Remove | Yes |

### Status Codes

```
2xx Success
├── 200 OK - Success with body
├── 201 Created - Resource created
├── 204 No Content - Success, no body

4xx Client Errors
├── 400 Bad Request - Invalid syntax
├── 401 Unauthorized - Auth missing
├── 403 Forbidden - Not authorized
├── 404 Not Found - Resource missing
├── 422 Unprocessable - Validation failed

5xx Server Errors
├── 500 Internal Error
└── 503 Service Unavailable
```

### Response Format

```typescript
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  data: T;
  meta?: {
    pagination?: { page, perPage, total };
    requestId: string;
  };
}

interface ApiError {
  error: {
    code: string;      // "VALIDATION_ERROR"
    message: string;   // Human-readable
    details?: Array<{ field, message }>;
  };
}
```

## GraphQL Design

### Types

```graphql
type User {
  id: ID!
  email: String!
  orders(first: Int, after: String): OrderConnection!
}

input CreateUserInput {
  email: String!
  name: String
}
```

### Mutations

```graphql
type Mutation {
  createUser(input: CreateUserInput!): CreateUserPayload!
}

type CreateUserPayload {
  user: User
  errors: [UserError!]
}
```

## Checklist

- [ ] Consistent naming conventions
- [ ] Consistent response structure
- [ ] Pagination on lists
- [ ] Authentication on non-public endpoints
- [ ] Rate limiting configured
- [ ] Input validation
